	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 743, footnote 187" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8381> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8381" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "See Cic. Mur. 36; Brut. 166." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6615> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6615" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 91 Attained all the highest offices (Cic. Off. 2.59). Not specific proof that he held the aedileship." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4179> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4179" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A Legate under Sulla, for whom he recovered Sardinia (Liv. Per. 86)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4060> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4060" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Verr. 2.1.143; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 54f., 130, 482f.; Val.. Max. 8.13.4; Plin. NH 7.156; Dio 41.14.5. In the lection of the Senate Philippus passed over his uncle Ap. Claudius Pulcher, one of the exiles (Cic. Dom. 84). L. Valerius Flaccus, the only living patrician censorius, was named Princeps Senatus (Liv. Per. 83; see 89, on M. Aemilius Scaurus), and the roll of citizens numbered 463,000 (Jerome, Chr. ad ann. 85, p.' 151 Helm)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4059> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4059" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "2 On the census, see ESAR 1.217, and Bennett, Cinna 44f. Censorinus (DN 23.7) refers to the placing of a sundial in the Forum by the Censor Marcius Philippus, but since Scipio Nasica is said to be Censor aliquanto post he may refer to Q. Marcius Philippus, Censor 164." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3800> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3800" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Lex Antonia de Termessensibus, CIL 12.2.589-ILS 38, cf. CIL 12.2.707; Cic. Com. 1, fr. 24, with Ascon. 68- 69C; Planc. 52; Diod. 37.2.2; Fast. Ant., Degrassi 164f., and Fast. Cap., ibid. 54f., 129, 480f.; Plin. NH 2.199; 33.55; Flor. 2.6.8; Obseq. 54; Eutrop. 5.3.1; Schol. Bob. 117f. Stangl; Oros. 5.18.1; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Cassiod.; and on Philippus, Auct. Vir. Ill. 66.9 and 12. Though at first a supporter of Livius Drusus, Philippus turned against him (Cic. De Or. 1.24; 2.220 and 255; 3.2; Prov. Cons. 21; Val. Max. 6.2.2; 9.5.2; Quintil. Inst. Or. 6.3.81; 11.1.37; Flor. 2.5.8-9; Auct. Vir. Ill. 66.9 and 12-13), and as Augur held that his legislation was invalid (Cic. Leg. 2.31; Com. 1, fr. 24, with Ascon. 69C; Val. Max. 9.5.2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3778> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3778" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Leg. 2.31; cf. Cic. Brut. 166; Ascon. In Corn. 69C." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3777> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3777" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "9 The collegium to which Marcius Philippus belonged in 93 (Cic. Brut. 166) is shown to be the college of Augurs by his actions as Consul and Augur in 91 (Cic. Leg. 2.3 1). The meaning of sodalitas remains obscure to me." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3723> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3723" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "2 Philippus, who was a rival of Herennius for the consulship in 93, must have held the praetorship by 96." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3564> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3564" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Proposed an agrariand law (Cic. Off. 2.73), and possibly a law to regulate procedure in prosecutions for usury (Gaius 4.23). See Niccolini, FTP 418." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/9983> rdfs:label "Post Assertion: #9983" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertion ;
